@D1D4K10 I do not have a info on this, I know Imavov is ready to go, the hold up for him versus Chimaev was the Ramadan initially then nursing an injury but now all of sudden he is ready to go, I heard Chimaev didn't wanted to fight him because of his muslim roots but there was no issue whatsoever on the Imavov side.
I know Khamzat is in America training.
If you ask me, the UFC is not on the business of meritocracy anymore, Imavov is not a fighter that gets fans excited in the UFC eyes and with Sean's recent performance, there is strong push for this fight right now.
